Algeria's President Abdelaziz Bouteflika drinking tea as he receives Algeria's Prime Minister Abdelmalek Sellal in a Paris hospital on June 12 2013 in one of the first pictures to emerge since he was hospitalised in France in April after a mini-str Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Algiers - Algeria's veteran President Abdelaziz Bouteflika travelled to France on Thursday for "regular medical tests", his office announced.It said in a statement that Bouteflika, 78, was making "a short, private visit during which he will undergo regular medical tests by his doctors".Bouteflika has ruled the oil-rich North African state since 1999, but concerns have been growing over how much longer he can stay in power.He won re-election last year but appeared only once during the campaign, in a wheelchair after suffering a stroke in 2013.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.